1. Course material
   The lesson texts, guides, documentation, course structure and original
   source code in this repository (the lrwros_* packages, scripts and labs)
   are provided to enrolled students of the Industrial ROS2 Manipulation Lab
   for personal learning, portfolio and professional use.

2. What students may do
   - Use, run, modify and adapt the code for personal and professional projects.
   - Publish their own capstone project based on this framework, with attribution.

3. What students may not do
   - Redistribute or resell the course lessons, guides or repository as a course
     or training product.

4. Third-party components
   Third-party packages pulled via the .repos files (Universal Robots
   description packages, Robotiq gripper packages, LinkAttacher, Fairino
   packages, and others) keep their own licenses. See
   00_inventory notes and .repos/ files for details. Nothing in this license
   overrides the licenses of third-party components.

